dct_title_s: Map of the route to Lhasa / compiled by Lt. Colonel Waddell.
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures and shading. Map shows lines of advance of the British Indian Army led by Colonel Sir Francis Edward Younghusband, sites of action or engagement, Fort or Jong are located.  Bogle, Turner & Mannings route through Bhotan. Map shows the route of advance of the British intervention in Tibet, 1900-4. Ancillary map: "Part of England on the same scale." Companion volume is available from RECAP. Call number: 1727 .949. A printed copy of this map is in volume.
